From: Stephen Gildea <mit-erl!gildea@mit-eddie.MIT.EDU>
Site: MIT Earth Resources Lab, Cambridge Mass.
Subject: rogue verses sysline
Index: 	games/rogue 4.2BSD

Description:
	The game of rogue requires that the screen be at least 24 lines long.
	This limit should be decreased to 23 so that people running
	sysline on the 24th line can still play rogue.
Repeat-By:
	Try to run rogue using a termcap entry that reserves the 24th
	line of the screen for sysline.

